This paper discusses association rule mining, which is a common task in data mining and database research. The paper focuses on the apriori algorithm, which is widely used in this area. Therefore, cs.DB (databases) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses variations of the algorithm that handle quantitative attributes and generalizations of items, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses pruning techniques, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses itemset correlation, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
